<h1>Problem 1509 - 2005 IMO, P1 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Six points are chosen on the sides of an equilateral triangle \(ABC\): \(A_1\), \(A_2\) on \(BC\), \(B_1\), \(B_2\) on \(CA\) and \(C_1\), \(C_2\) on \(AB\), such that they are the vertices of a convex hexagon \(A_1A_2B_1B_2C_1C_2\) with equal side lengths.</p>
<p>Prove that the lines \(A_1B_2\), \(B_1C_2\) and \(C_1A_2\) are concurrent.</p>
